Nigerian singer-songwriter Kizz Daniel’s hit song, Buga, has continued to gain local and global acceptance since its release. Aside from creating a buzz on Tik Tok and becoming the most Shazamed song, the song has continued to get on every music chart. “It’s a great feeling. When you put out a masterpiece and the rest of the world accepts it as one, that’s a satisfying feeling right there. And such encourages you to do more,” Kizz Daniel says of the song.   Yetunde Barnabas, Peter Olayinka expecting first child     Peter Obi’s supporters may be unable to pay cost of…     Why I wooed Pete Davidson, by Kim Kardashian   Continuing, he said, “Buga, many music tasters, have said, “As long as people work so hard to make legit money, they should be proud to flaunt their wealth to the public.” The singer left fans asking for more as he performed at the 02 Arena and in Birmingham before embarking on a tour of the U.S., Australia, and Europe. On the acceptance and turnout of his London tour, he said: “After the London tour, I’ll still be on the road. I want to connect to my fans worldwide. The US Tour is next followed by Africa, Australia, Europe etc.”